<tr bgcolor="#333366"><td valign="bottom" colspan="2" class="clsBoldWhite">&nbsp;&nbsp;New IRL forum</b></td></tr>
<tr bgcolor="#9999cc"><td valign="bottom" class="clsSmall">&nbsp;<i>Kocho Divah</i></td><td valign="bottom" align="right" class="clsSmall">&nbsp;&nbsp;Tuesday, February 11, 2003&nbsp;&nbsp;1:34pm CST</b></td></tr>
<tr><td colspan="2" bgcolor="#eeeeee"><br><blockquote>Yeah, I just cleared out 75% of our forums, but I've added a very important one.<br><br>I think of EQDiva as a nice community to hang out in. I'm adding an IRL (In real life) forum for us to get to know each other better, and blab about everyday life. <br><br>I'm trying to follow my server forums. There, we've gotten to know each other almost intimately. We talk about reviews (movie, book, games, products), opinions, and learn so much from each other. It's a great form of entertainment that can take your mind off of EQ for a few minutes.<br><br>If you're EQ retired but addicted to the social aspect of forums, then you've got a reason to hang with us again.<br><br><a href='http://pub142.ezboard.com/feqdivabardsofeverquestfrm85'>IRL Forum</a><br></blockquote></td></tr>
